Name: alcoholic psychosis
Definition: An alcohol-induced mental disorder involving prominent hallucinations and delusions occurring during or shortly after acute alcohol intoxication or withdrawal.

Name: obsolete abnormal glucose tolerance in mother complicating pregnancy childbirth and/or puerperium
Definition: An alcohol-induced mental disorder involving prominent hallucinations and delusions occurring during or shortly after acute alcohol intoxication or withdrawal.
Synonym: postpartum abnormal glucose tolerance of mother
